      {
         "id": "SECTION_babylon",
         "text": [
            {
               "text": "<p><h3>O Cativeiro Babilônico</h3>Determinar o início do período do cativeiro Babilônico é uma tarefa complexa (<htcite0> ; <htcite1>). Segundo as crônicas babilônicas, sabemos que:",
               "source": [
                  {
                     "type": 1,
                     "uuid": "e983fb3b-ddac-42ca-8f72-7fa8695071d0",
                     "text": "Britannica, T. Editors of Encyclopaedia",
                     "page": "",
                     "date_time": {
                        "type": "gregory",
                        "year": "2024",
                        "month": "06",
                        "day": "23"
                     }
                  },
                  {
                     "type": 1,
                     "uuid": "dcea1506-7ce0-4244-8050-91dc1cdf9547",
                     "text": "Horn, S. H",
                     "page": "pp. 13 - 15",
                     "date_time": {
                        "type": "gregory",
                        "year": "1967",
                        "month": "06",
                        "day": "23"
                     }
                  }
               ],
               "date_time": [
                  {
                     "type": "gregory",
                     "year": "2024",
                     "month": "5",
                     "day": "3"
                  },
                  {
                     "type": "gregory",
                     "year": "1967",
                     "month": "-1",
                     "day": "-1"
                  }
               ],
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "html",
               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "<p><ul class=\"citation\"> <li> <i>Nabucodonosor partiu para a Palestina (Hatti-land) em Kislev do seu 7º ano de reinado (= <htdate0>) e conquistou \"a cidade de Judá\" (= Jerusalém) em 2 de Adar (= <htdate1>). Além disso, afirma-se que naquele dia ele \"capturou o rei\" e \"nomeou ali um rei de sua escolha\". Isso fornece uma data exata para o fim do reinado de Joaquim e a ascensão de Zedequias (<htcite0>).</i> </li></li></ul> </p>",
               "source": [
                  {
                     "type": 1,
                     "uuid": "dcea1506-7ce0-4244-8050-91dc1cdf9547",
                     "text": "Horn, S. H",
                     "page": "pp. 20 - 21",
                     "date_time": {
                        "type": "gregory",
                        "year": "1967",
                        "month": "06",
                        "day": "23"
                     }
                  }
               ],
               "date_time": [
                  {
                     "type": "gregory",
                     "year": "-598",
                     "month": "-1",
                     "day": "-1"
                  },
                  {
                     "type": "gregory",
                     "year": "-597",
                     "month": "-1",
                     "day": "-1"
                  },
                  {
                     "type": "gregory",
                     "year": "-586",
                     "month": "-1",
                     "day": "-1"
                  }
               ],
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "html",
               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "<p>Com base nas crônicas babilônicas e nos livros judaicos, podemos concluir que a queda de Jerusalém ocorreu em <htdate0> com a deportação dos judeus acontecendo nesse intervalo de tempo (<htcite0> ; <htcite1> ; <htcite2> ; <htcite3> ; <htcite4>).</p>",
               "source": [
                  {
                     "type": 1,
                     "uuid": "dcea1506-7ce0-4244-8050-91dc1cdf9547",
                     "text": "Horn, S. H",
                     "page": "pp. 24 - 27",
                     "date_time": {
                        "type": "gregory",
                        "year": "1967",
                        "month": "06",
                        "day": "23"
                     }
                  },
                  {
                     "type": 1,
                     "uuid": "83959c73-67dd-4706-82f2-6435e1610e00",
                     "text": "Mark, J. J.",
                     "page": "Nebuchadnezzar II",
                     "date_time": {
                        "type": "gregory",
                        "year": "2018",
                        "month": "06",
                        "day": "23"
                     }
                  },
                  {
                     "type": 2,
                     "uuid": "56e19b6d-5b12-4a9d-abff-7c85ff465872",
                     "text": "Torah, Neviim u-Khetuvim. Twenty-four books of the Holy Scriptures carefully translated according to the Massoretic text, on the basis of the English version, after the best Jewish authorities, , 2º Reis 24:14-16",
                     "page": "pp. 466",
                     "date_time": {
                        "type": "gregory",
                        "year": "1891",
                        "month": "03",
                        "day": "03"
                     }
                  },
                  {
                     "type": 2,
